## Context-rich play handoffs outperform generic recommendations

Play execution improved when recommendations included triggering evidence and
stakeholder context, not just a play label.

Fact: Plays with evidence-linked context produced higher execution follow-through.
Belief: Recommendation quality depends on contextual narrative, not taxonomy match alone.
Value: Human operators need clear "why now" context to trust agent suggestions.
Precedent: Prior rollout reviews showed higher adoption for evidence-backed play prompts.
